 className="absolute top-0 right-0 z-20 group pointer-events-auto"
 ```
 and
 ```css
 className="absolute top-16 right-0 z-10 group pointer-events-auto"
 ```

This solution works by:
- Making the entire floating button container transparent to mouse events (`pointer-events-none`), so clicks will pass through to elements underneath it
- Re-enabling mouse events only for the actual buttons themselves (`pointer-events-auto`), so they remain clickable

Now, when users interact with components near the floating icons, they'll be able to click through the transparent parts of the container to reach elements underneath, while still being able to click directly on the floating icons when needed."}]}]}}
